recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Directive 75/268/EEC of 28 April 1975 on mountain and hill farming and farming in certain less-favoured areas (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 797/85 (2), and in particular Article 2 (3) thereof,
Whereas Council Directive 75/271/EEC of 28 April 1975 concerning the Community list of less-favoured areas within the meaning of Directive 75/271/EEC (3), as last amended by Directive 86/655/EEC (4), describes the regions of France included on the Community list of less-favoured areas within the meaning of Article 3 (3), (4) and (5) of Directive 75/268/EEC;
Whereas the French Government has requested, pursuant to Article 2 (1) of Directive 75/268/EEC, an amendment to the limits of the less-favoured areas listed in the Annex to Directive 75/271/EEC;
Whereas the partial classification of a new commune and the transfer of certain areas already included on the list of areas within the meaning of Article 3 (4) and (5) of Directive 75/268/EEC to the list of areas within the meaning of Article 3 (3) of that Directive comply with the indications and the figures, including the criteria for exceptions, adopted by Directive 75/271/EEC for the demarcation of mountain and hill areas;
Whereas the set of amendments requested by the French Government under Article 2 (3) of Directive 75/268/EEC does not lead to an increase in the total utilized agricultural area of the less-favoured areas and consequently has no effect on the limit laid down in that Article;
Whereas the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF) Committee has been consulted on the Agricultural Structure;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Decision are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Agricultural Structure,
